# Design laws — "Calm Garden" (UI/UX is the top priority)

Authoritative token spec: `docs/ai/design-system.md` (read it before building or
changing any UI). Token values live in `src/styles/globals.css`. Visual source of
truth: `docs/design/references/`.

## Non-negotiables

- Minimal first: reduce to essentials, whitespace is a feature, one primary action per screen.
- One typeface (Inter); hierarchy via weight/size only — never add a second display font.
- Theme = "flowers & sunlight", LIGHT by default: a warm sunlit cream canvas (with a
  soft ambient sun-glow) + warm near-black ink + ONE accent, and the accent is the
  PER-HABIT color. App chrome stays warm and quiet; a habit's color appears only inside
  its own card/ring/streak/check. The FAB/primary CTA uses ink, not an accent.
- Borders are hairlines; elevation is subtle. No heavy drop shadows; no gradient fills
  on components or text (one subtle ambient background glow on the canvas is allowed).
- Corners: cards ~20px, controls 12px, circular for rings/avatars/checks/FAB.
- Spacing on a 4px scale (8/12/16/20/24/32); 16-20px card padding and screen gutters.
- Use tabular numbers for streaks, XP, and stats.
- Light by default; a dark theme is deferred to later theming. Never hardcode colors —
  consume the design tokens (CSS vars / Tailwind theme).

## Motion

- Feedback only: 120-240ms; spring on check-off and ring-fill. Celebrations (confetti) < 900ms and optional.
- ALWAYS respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Honest gamification (never an arcade)

- Anchor every element (XP, streak, badge) to a REAL completed action in the data model, not taps.
- NEVER punish a missed day and never use guilt copy — offer a gentle streak-freeze or "start fresh".
- Reserve badges for meaningful milestones; introduce mechanics sparingly (rings + streaks + XP first). No leaderboards.
- Never signal state with color alone — pair with an icon, label, or fill.

## Accessibility (required)

- Contrast >= 4.5:1; tap targets >= 44px; visible focus rings; `rem` units; semantic HTML + aria-labels on icon buttons.

## Workflow

- Use Tailwind v4 tokens + shadcn/ui primitives (restyle, don't hand-roll). Keep components small and composable.
- Any UI change must stay consistent with `docs/ai/design-system.md`; update that spec if the design genuinely evolves.
